place.name: UPTON
place.gazetteerText: UPTON, a parish, with a village, in Blofield district, Norfolk; 1¼ mile NNW of Acle, and 5 NE of Brundall r. station. Post town, Acle. Acres, 1,693. Real property, with Fishley, £4,489. Pop. of U. alone, 601. Houses, 127. The property is much subdivided. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Ranworth. The church is old. There are a Primitive Methodist chapel, and a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
